XYVision Inc is issuing a 25 mln dlrconvertible eurobond due May 5, 2002 paying an indicated couponof between 5-3/4 and six pct and priced at par, lead managerCredit Suisse First Boston Ltd said.    The issue is callable after 30 days at 106 pct declining byone pct per annum to par thereafter. It is not callable forthree years unless the conversion price exceeds the stock priceby 130 pct.    The selling concession is 1-1/2 pct while management andunderwriting each pay 1/2 pct. Final terms will be set on, orbefore, April 15.    The issue is available in bearer and registered form indenominations of 5,000 dlrs. It will be listed in Luxembourgwhile the payment date is May 5. REUTER&#3;